From the resemblance of ‘pudor’ and ‘pudicitia‚’ a careless transcriber might readily allow one of them to drop out, or a half- learned copyist might designedly omit ‘pudicitia,’ regarding it as synonymous with ⁸ pudor? This, however, strictly speaking, is not the case. ‘Pudor’ and ‘Pudicitia’ are connected as cause and effect. ‘Pudor’ is, properly, the principle of modesty, which produces ‘ Pudi- citia’ or purity of conduct-‘Pudor’ belongs to the mind, ‘ Pudicitia’ to the body.
